Git Commands:
================

Basic Commands

1. git init - will create new local git repository
2. git clone - is used to copy a repository
3. git add - add file as it looks now to your next commit(stage)
4. git commit  -m "message"- will create a snapshot of the changes and save it to the git
5. git push - publish local changes to the original

Make a change

1. git status - list new or modified files not yet committed
2. git diff list down changes and conflicts
3. git reset - unstages file, keeping the file changes

Branching and Merging

1. git branch - will list your branches
2. git checkout - switch to another brnach and check it out into your working directory
3. git merge - will merge the specified branch's history into the current branch
4. git log - show all commmits in the current branch's history


Synchronize

git remote add <name> <url> - create new connection to a remote repo
git fetch - get all the changes from the origin
git pull - get all teh latest chagnes from the origin and merge
